Memba district has high levels of multidimensional poverty and many of its youth have been recruited by insurgent groups fighting in neighbouring Cabo Delgado province, often for small financial incentives. The district has strong potential for fisheries and is located close to the deep water port of Nacala. the project have an Hybrid design combining two years of $40 monthly flow payments to 3900 households with a one-time $250 transfer to all (estimated 2900) youth across those households.

Mogovolas district has high levels of multidimensional poverty (approx. 79%) yet sits on good agricultural land for production of livestock and cashew nuts. Most people are engaged in subsistence farming but some farmers are transitioning into semi-commercial enterprises. The project will target approx 4,300 households will receive investment-sized transfers (total value $1,000) timed to coincide with key moments in the agricultural calendar: planting and harvesting. RESINA will intensify distribution of inputs and technologies at the same time.

Strengthen the resilience of IDPs and host communities living in fragile contexts by using unconditional cash transfers to bridge the gap between relief and recovery, and facilitate the transition off of humanitarian support. By addressing immediate needs and providing capital for long-term investments, the program aims to empower IDPs to actively participate in shaping their economic recovery and positively impact their well-being and prospects for the future.
